        <h2>Step 3: MOFA Attestation in the UAE</h2>

        <p>Your document now has a US apostille and UAE Embassy attestation. The final authentication step happens in the UAE itself: <strong>MOFA (Ministry of Foreign Affairs) attestation</strong>.</p>

        <p>This is the UAE government's final stamp of approval. Without it, no government entity, court, or official body in the UAE will accept your document.</p>

        <h3>Where MOFA-Attested Documents Are Required</h3>

        <ul class="acceptance-list">
          <li><i class="fas fa-gavel"></i> <strong>Courts:</strong> Marriage registration, divorce proceedings, custody cases</li>
          <li><i class="fas fa-passport"></i> <strong>Immigration (ICP/GDRFA):</strong> Residency visas, family sponsorship, Golden Visa</li>
